WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.880
- Say hi again to the people.

00:00:01.880 --> 00:00:04.640
- All right, okay, hi camera, hi everybody.

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:06.740
I'm John Lindblad, I'm from WSo

00:00:06.740 --> 00:00:07.220
cial.

00:00:07.220 --> 00:00:10.970
And if you heard the previous session from Gander, there

00:00:10.970 --> 00:00:13.440
's gonna be a lot of similarities here.

00:00:13.440 --> 00:00:16.330
WSocial is also a new social medium being started up

00:00:16.360 --> 00:00:19.660
in the same sort of context that we just heard.

00:00:19.660 --> 00:00:22.240
And we are also very adamant about the ability to be

00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:24.840
able to trust your feed and maybe quiet things down a little

00:00:25.010 --> 00:00:25.220
bit.

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:30.240
So we sort of want to go back to what the golden

00:00:30.240 --> 00:00:34.030
age when Twitter was new and actually useful, where we had

00:00:34.030 --> 00:00:40.010
common understanding and global discussion that we could really participate in in

00:00:40.080 --> 00:00:40.990
a useful way.

00:00:41.020 --> 00:00:45.830
We are all for real humans, quality journalism and open debate

00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:46.100
.

00:00:46.100 --> 00:00:48.940
So why now?

00:00:48.940 --> 00:00:51.310
Well, I don't need to go into this so much

00:00:51.340 --> 00:00:51.340
.

00:00:51.340 --> 00:00:54.720
You, we already know the situation in the world and in

00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:58.180
Europe, just as here in Canada, there is a lot

00:00:58.220 --> 00:01:02.740
of strong feelings about having something that's independent and that nobody

00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:04.520
should be able to shut down.

00:01:04.520 --> 00:01:06.090
But we don't want to be separatist, just

00:01:06.090 --> 00:01:07.140
like most other people.

00:01:07.160 --> 00:01:10.490
We want to be part of the whole ecosystem here, but

00:01:10.540 --> 00:01:16.960
not being dependent on certain pieces here that we don't control

00:01:16.980 --> 00:01:17.230
.

00:01:17.240 --> 00:01:19.970
So I'll mention some core principles.

00:01:19.980 --> 00:01:23.330
So we are hosted in Europe, both when it comes to

00:01:23.330 --> 00:01:26.480
ownership and the actual hosting and all the services.

00:01:26.480 --> 00:01:28.980
We verify humans, I'll come back to that.

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:32.340
We want to be open and transparent.

00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:34.560
So show exactly what we are doing and why we're doing

00:01:34.570 --> 00:01:35.060
things.

00:01:35.060 --> 00:01:41.180
We want to allow free speech according to European laws and norms

00:01:41.180 --> 00:01:41.470
.

00:01:41.480 --> 00:01:45.430
We don't want to be interfering in what people say and

00:01:45.430 --> 00:01:46.160
stuff.

00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:47.160
Everybody should have their voice.

00:01:47.160 --> 00:01:49.660
That's why we go back to these verified humans.

00:01:49.660 --> 00:01:53.440
Anybody who is a human should have this democratic right to say

00:01:53.450 --> 00:01:54.610
whatever they want.

00:01:54.620 --> 00:01:58.470
Then as a participant in this network, you also have your

00:01:58.470 --> 00:02:01.260
right to choose what to listen to or not listen to,

00:02:01.290 --> 00:02:01.700
of course.

00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:06.860
So democracy is very important to us.

00:02:10.340 --> 00:02:12.960
We want to be good at Prado citizens.

00:02:12.960 --> 00:02:15.340
If we, we are pretty new to this.

00:02:15.340 --> 00:02:17.080
So if we goof, let us know.

00:02:17.100 --> 00:02:22.070
We of course wanted to start on at Prado, both

00:02:22.070 --> 00:02:24.830
from the sort of political point of view, this is the

00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:26.820
right thing to do, but this is also just as we

00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:31.060
noticed a cold start problem without 40 million users would be difficult

00:02:31.060 --> 00:02:31.240
.

00:02:31.240 --> 00:02:33.070
So it's a no brainer really.

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:37.140
Okay, verified humans.

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:38.140
You have already seen this.

00:02:38.140 --> 00:02:39.380
This is a solved problem, right?

00:02:39.420 --> 00:02:41.790
You just check that box and we know it's human.

00:02:41.840 --> 00:02:44.620
Maybe.

00:02:44.620 --> 00:02:50.290
No, so we really want to verify that your users are

00:02:50.290 --> 00:02:50.660
human.

00:02:50.660 --> 00:02:53.620
Or we will allow bots and organizations and things like this too

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:55.100
, but they will be marked as such.

00:02:55.100 --> 00:02:57.860
This is an organization, this is a bot and so on

00:02:57.860 --> 00:02:58.190
.

00:02:58.200 --> 00:03:01.460
So we actually go all the way to scanning passports or

00:03:01.460 --> 00:03:02.900
ID documents.

00:03:02.900 --> 00:03:08.500
So when you click on that little ID badge next to your

00:03:08.500 --> 00:03:11.000
name, you will be able to see things about who you

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:11.450
are.

00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:13.320
You will see at least, right now, it's only

00:03:13.330 --> 00:03:15.990
showing that you are a human, but it will show more

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:19.680
things about you that you want to share.

00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:21.100
You can also be anonymous here.

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:23.220
You don't have to share your real name, but we

00:03:23.220 --> 00:03:25.140
will know that you are a human.

00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:27.140
And how can we know that you're a human and not

00:03:27.170 --> 00:03:28.800
knowing who you are?

00:03:28.800 --> 00:03:31.480
Actually, I have this PDS call here.

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:34.840
You can see that when you get your profile, you can

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:36.640
tell that somebody is a human here.

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:42.940
Yeah, we are building the whole system up into two separate

00:03:42.980 --> 00:03:44.210
domains.

00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:49.040
We have one part of the system, actually a separate company

00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:51.680
, that is running something called Widentity.

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:54.140
And Widentity, that's the one that's scanning

00:03:54.140 --> 00:03:58.240
your passport and storing locally in the phone who you are.

00:03:58.240 --> 00:04:01.530
It will know your nationality, birth date, full name

00:04:01.540 --> 00:04:01.840
.

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:05.220
In some countries, it will know your social security number.

00:04:05.220 --> 00:04:07.440
It will have the face of your photo, photo of your

00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:08.120
face.

00:04:09.220 --> 00:04:12.930
But it will not share that with WSocial.

00:04:12.940 --> 00:04:16.500
So WSocial is a separate app, separate company that

00:04:16.500 --> 00:04:21.090
knows, of course, everything that you know about your online

00:04:21.090 --> 00:04:24.150
life, your posts, your friends, your likes, and

00:04:24.150 --> 00:04:24.680
all that.

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:26.780
But they will not know who you are.

00:04:26.780 --> 00:04:29.110
The only thing that unifies these two is this UU

00:04:29.110 --> 00:04:33.540
ID, 32 digit hex random number, basically.

00:04:33.560 --> 00:04:37.510
So if you are on the WID side, identity side

00:04:37.510 --> 00:04:39.930
, you will know that this is a human, but not

00:04:39.930 --> 00:04:41.420
who it is on social media.

00:04:41.420 --> 00:04:43.960
And on WSocial, you will know that this is

00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:46.350
somebody, that's a real human, but not who that

00:04:46.480 --> 00:04:46.700
is.

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:52.910
We also bring over nationality and birth year, or actually

00:04:52.910 --> 00:04:54.760
that's, we are planning to, we are not doing

00:04:54.760 --> 00:04:55.580
that right now.

00:04:55.580 --> 00:04:58.340
And optionally, somebody who really wants to verify, I

00:04:58.340 --> 00:05:03.690
am really this person, should have an ability to verify that

00:05:03.690 --> 00:05:06.780
this is my real name, if they want to.

00:05:06.780 --> 00:05:07.880
Some people might want to.

00:05:07.880 --> 00:05:10.920
Who are we?

00:05:10.920 --> 00:05:14.500
We are about two dozen people spread out over Europe.

00:05:14.500 --> 00:05:17.800
WSocial is incorporated in Stockholm, or actually it's

00:05:17.810 --> 00:05:20.280
not incorporated, it's a foundation.

00:05:20.280 --> 00:05:23.430
So it's a foundation that owns these two companies, the

00:05:23.450 --> 00:05:27.000
W Identity Company and the WSocial Company.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:29.220
We have a CEO, Anna Zeiter.

00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:35.480
She has a background as privacy executive at eBay, and she

00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:38.420
has a PhD in free speech and data, GDPR and

00:05:38.420 --> 00:05:39.900
all those things.

00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:41.780
Legal kind of background.

00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:43.520
And I'm just a developer.

00:05:43.520 --> 00:05:50.170
Business model, okay, so we will have some advertisements at

00:05:50.170 --> 00:05:51.740
some point in the future, we think.

00:05:51.740 --> 00:05:55.000
And having verified human users is a good thing, because the

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:58.230
advertisers typically want to pay more for ads for humans than for

00:05:58.230 --> 00:05:58.900
ads for bots.

00:05:58.900 --> 00:06:02.970
And we also, since we have this W Identity app

00:06:02.980 --> 00:06:05.360
that really knows who you are, and you can connect that

00:06:05.370 --> 00:06:08.390
app to wallets and banks and stuff, it will be

00:06:08.430 --> 00:06:10.520
easy for us to add micropayments.

00:06:10.520 --> 00:06:13.230
So that's really something that we're working on, especially

00:06:13.230 --> 00:06:14.630
for news media.

00:06:14.700 --> 00:06:16.380
So we want to work with the news medias.

00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:20.530
We have negotiations ongoing with a number of different European media houses

00:06:20.540 --> 00:06:23.410
for how we should not steal their content, but really provide

00:06:23.410 --> 00:06:24.740
the platform for their content.

00:06:24.740 --> 00:06:32.400
So we want to redistribute, work together with media

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:32.930
sites.

00:06:32.940 --> 00:06:35.300
What did we do?

00:06:35.300 --> 00:06:39.720
Okay, we launched this project in January in Davos.

00:06:39.740 --> 00:06:44.400
And within one week of the announcement, we noticed on our

00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:49.660
social media monitoring dashboards that we had 1 billion social media

00:06:49.670 --> 00:06:52.060
views of posts that mentioned W Social.

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:54.240
So some attention seems to have come our way.

00:06:54.240 --> 00:07:00.920
Yeah, and we're just taking in the first few users

00:07:00.930 --> 00:07:01.710
this week.

00:07:01.720 --> 00:07:04.510
We want to scale it up a little bit slowly so let

00:07:04.540 --> 00:07:06.520
's see that our infrastructure holds up.

00:07:08.240 --> 00:07:11.950
And the next steps here, so around May timeframe or so

00:07:11.960 --> 00:07:15.460
, we think that we will be opening up for the wait

00:07:15.460 --> 00:07:16.030
list.

00:07:16.040 --> 00:07:20.030
We have a waitlist and then open up for anybody without

00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:22.510
any sort of invitation codes around that time.

00:07:22.580 --> 00:07:30.020
And what we hope to do with you here is of course

00:07:30.020 --> 00:07:30.820
, we want to say hello.

00:07:30.840 --> 00:07:33.420
We are glad to be here among at Prada friends.

00:07:34.060 --> 00:07:37.100
And if anybody wants to come with some ideas, proposals,

00:07:37.100 --> 00:07:38.780
questions, or whatever it is, just say hello.

00:07:38.780 --> 00:07:40.020
Come to me and we'll talk.

00:07:40.020 --> 00:07:43.480
This talk is coming to an end so it will have to

00:07:43.480 --> 00:07:45.040
be offline or afterwards.

00:07:45.040 --> 00:07:48.980
We really want to be good at Prada citizens.

00:07:48.980 --> 00:07:51.740
And since we're new to this, we're probably going

00:07:51.740 --> 00:07:53.040
to do a few things wrong.

00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:55.700
I already, during this couple of days here, noticed a

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:57.860
few things that I should have done differently.

00:07:59.240 --> 00:08:01.910
We'll fix that whenever you see something that's a bit

00:08:01.920 --> 00:08:04.880
strange or perhaps even bad, let us know.

00:08:04.880 --> 00:08:09.060
And we know that a lot of the things that we aspire

00:08:09.060 --> 00:08:12.420
to do on at Prado is already maybe happening somewhere,

00:08:12.420 --> 00:08:15.500
like for example, there's permission data and stuff like that

00:08:15.550 --> 00:08:15.760
.

00:08:15.960 --> 00:08:18.990
So let us know when we should be taking part in something

00:08:18.990 --> 00:08:19.780
like that.

00:08:19.780 --> 00:08:23.340
And we also have a few ideas, especially around this,

00:08:23.340 --> 00:08:28.190
when it comes to account certification, verification, and account types

00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:28.420
.

00:08:28.420 --> 00:08:29.800
So this is a human account.

00:08:29.820 --> 00:08:32.710
We want to have some sort of commonly agreed upon way to

00:08:32.780 --> 00:08:38.160
express that so that everybody in the atmosphere can tell.

00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:40.740
Wish us luck.

00:08:40.740 --> 00:08:45.160
Thank you.
